xcept 2016/17 which is based on revised data.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-04-23T16:22:53.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882200/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882200/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882200/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-13","Reading: Lewisham Deptford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many and what proportion of pupils (a) attained and (b) exceeded the minimum standard for reading at (i) key stage 1 and (ii) key stage 2 in Lewisham, Deptford constituency in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","135271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882201","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>There has been no recent assessment of the adequacy of National Minimum Allowances for foster parents in covering the cost of raising children.</p><p> </p><p>‘Foster Care in England’, the independent review of the fostering system and the Education Select Committee made a number of recommendations relating to the support foster parents receive, including financial support. We are carefully considering the recommendations made by both reports and the government response will be published in spring this year.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-04-23T16:55:29.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882201/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882201/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882201/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-13","Foster Care: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent assessment he has made of the adequacy of foster care allowances in covering the cost of raising children.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","135272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882202","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-19","<p>This information is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>Whilst the Mental Health Services Data Set (MHSDS) collects information on waiting times from referral to treatment, MHSDS cannot separately identify those people referred into services for an assessment for Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","135274 ; 135275","2018-04-19T11:09:16.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882202/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882202/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882202/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-13","Hyperactivity: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many people aged under 18 are awaiting assessment for attention deficit or hyperactivity disorder in (a) Kent, (b) West Yorkshire and (c) Greater Manchester.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","135273"
