"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882266","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Gambling Commission measures participation in gambling activity and the problem gambling rates associated with the activity. The latest Great Britain wide data on gambling participation and problem gambling rates is set out in the Health Survey report on Gambling Behaviour in Great Britain 2015, published in August 2017. This report found that 10% of people over the age of 16 participated in online gambling or betting in the past year and, amongst those, problem gambling rates were 5.1%.</p><p> </p><p>The report is available here: http://live-gamblecom.cloud.contensis.com/PDF/survey-data/Gambling-behaviour-in-Great-Britain-2015.pdf</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2018-04-23T16:09:54.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882266/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882266/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882266/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-13","Gambling: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate his Department has made of the number of people addicted to online gambling services.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","135378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882267","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-04-19","<p>The Legal Ombudsman - an arm’s length body overseen by the Ministry of Justice - is independent in making decisions on individual cases. The Secretary of State for Justice is confident that the Legal Ombudsman operates an effective review process.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-04-19T14:54:59.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882267/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882267/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882267/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-13","Legal Ombudsman","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department has made an assessment of the effectiveness of the Legal Ombudsmen's review process.","false","Biography information for Ruth George","High Peak","Ruth George","135388"
