"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882269","Department for Education","false","2018-04-23","<p>The Student Loans Company, which administers Disabled Students’ Allowances, maintains records of payments made to non-medical help (NMH) providers but does not record information by provider on NMH referrals.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-04-23T13:49:20.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882269/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882269/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882269/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-13","Disabled Students' Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many non-medical help providers have had (a) no referrals, (b) fewer than five referrals and (c) fewer than 10 referrals since the introduction of the Disabled Students Allowance Quality Assurance Group list in April 2016.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","135391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882270","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-04-18","<p>The Law Commission’s report, Technical Issues in Charity Law makes a number of recommendations for simplifying charity law. We are giving the report’s recommendations full consideration and will respond in due course. Primary Legislation would be required to implement many of the report’s recommendations, and the Charity Commission would need additional resources to update its systems and guidance.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2018-04-18T12:44:22.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882270/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882270/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882270/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-13","Charities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with references to Technical Issues in Charity Law, published by the Law Commission in September 2017, whether he plans to take steps in response to the recommendations in that report.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","135395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882271","Department for Education","false","2018-04-18","<p>Any exclusion of a pupil, even for a short period of time, must be formally recorded.</p><p>The head teacher of a school can only exclude a pupil on disciplinary grounds. The decision to exclude a pupil must be lawful, reasonable and fair.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not hold the information on any children who have been prevented from attending school outside of this process.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-04-18T16:26:38.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882271/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882271/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/882271/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-13","Pupil Exclusions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children were informally excluded from schools in academic year 2016-17; and how many of those informal exclusions related to SEND children.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","135397"
